Thank you Mr. Huntsman. You represent the very best of Utah and humankind. May God bless you, your family and the legacy you leave behind. We are better because of you.

Here‚Äôs the thing, after today I realize that he made everyone feel like me. Notice how many tributes mention him as a personal friend or mentor. That‚Äôs the true mark of a leader. The Billionaire Philanthropist cared about the one.

Finally we made it to his office where we sat and talked about public service, leadership and political philosophy. Before I left he gave me a handwritten note of appreciation. His warmth & love was profound. I was stunned.

For the next NINETY MINUTES this giant-among-men told me dozens of personal stories about his wife‚Äôs family from Fairview, Richard Nixon, Beanie Babies, Margaret Thatcher, McDonalds, the Pope and so many more. All while walking arm-in-arm around the building.

I soon heard a baritone voice singing a song about ‚Äúbeautiful Sanpete County.‚Äù We had never met before but he gave me a big hug. He needed support to walk, but asked his assistant to leave us. He locked arms w me and took me on a tour.

So many thoughts on the passing of Jon Huntsman Sr. I haven‚Äôt shared this before, but soon after becoming Lt. Gov he wrote me a letter and invited me to come and see him. I had no idea what to expect when I arrived at Huntsman headquarters.
